ed_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What happened?\r\n\r\nI need to replace `release.github.owner` with a template action (`{{ .Env.GITHUB_REPOSITORY_OWNER}}')`)\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/rfay/junk/blob/cdc7e898179ae6857b3ae14e042fac22f613aa2b/.goreleaser.yml#L8\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\n  github:\r\n    owner: \"{{ .Env.GITHUB_REPOSITORY_OWNER }}\"\r\n    name: junk\r\n```\r\n\r\n`export GITHUB_REPOSITORY_OWNER=rfay` and then\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ goreleaser release --rm-dist\r\n   • by using this software you agree with its EULA, available at https://goreleaser.com/eula\r\n   • running goreleaser v1.9.2-pro\r\n  ...\r\n   • publishing\r\n      • scm releases\r\n         • creating or updating release repo={{ .Env.GITHUB_REPOSITORY_OWNER }}/junk tag=v0.3\r\n         • release updated           url=\r\n   ⨯ release failed after 0.79s error=scm releases: failed to publish artifacts: POST https://api.github.com/repos/%7B%7B%20.Env.GITHUB_REPOSITORY_OWNER%20%7D%7D/junk/releases: 404 Not Found []\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that it's trying to push without replacing the environment variable, so it fails.\r\n\r\nThis same replacement does in fact work in `brews` and `aurs`.\r\n\r\n### How can we reproduce this?\r\n\r\n* Check out https://github.com/rfay/junk\r\n* Change the details as necessary to something you have access to\r\n* `export GITHUB_REPOSITORY_OWNER=you\r\n* `goreleaser release --rm-dist`\r\n\r\n### goreleaser version\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ngoreleaser version 1.9.2-pro\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### GoReleaser Check\r\n\r\n- [X] goreleaser check shows no errors\r\n\r\n### Search\r\n\r\n- [X] I did search for other open and closed issues before opening this.\r\n\r\n### Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_","closed_by":{"login":"caarlos0","id":245435,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0NTQzNQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/245435?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.g